[00:00:31.118] Browser LOG     API BOOKS: [{"__v":0,"_id":"69cff5301701d3702c9ec4b4","author":"Rev Vincent Mboya","coverImage":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dexy2tumo/image/upload/v1775236400/books/covers/znwrpdpt3fv4e1fpjnew.jpg","createdAt":"2026-04-03T17:13:20.789Z","description":"Polygamy explores the practice of having multiple spouses, examining its biblical, cultural, and social dimensions. The book discusses the historical context of polygamy in Scripture, the ethical and moral questions it raises, and its impact on families and communities. It provides readers with insight into how different societies and Christian teachings view polygamy, offering guidance on navigating this complex and often controversial subject.","fileUrl":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dexy2tumo/raw/upload/v1775236399/books/files/fy13v2umkuudp5rgd9oo","price":200,"title":"Polygamy","updatedAt":"2026-04-07T12:14:05.573Z"},{"__v":0,"_id":"69cff47e1701d3702c9ec4af","author":"undefined","coverImage":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dexy2tumo/image/upload/v1775236221/books/covers/rc9a7px0c4m0xhrtre68.jpg","createdAt":"2026-04-03T17:10:22.132Z","description":"Water Baptism is a Christian guide that explores the sacred practice of baptism, explaining its spiritual significance, biblical foundation, and role in the life of a believer. The book teaches how baptism symbolizes repentance, cleansing from sin, and new life in Christ, while examining the different practices and beliefs across Christian denominations. It provides practical insight into how and why baptism is performed, helping readers understand its importance as both a personal and communal act of faith.","fileUrl":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dexy2tumo/raw/upload/v1775236221/books/files/gmsk206udbvxe1cn2uir","price":200,"title":"Water Baptism","updatedAt":"2026-04-07T12:14:34.663Z"},{"__v":0,"_id":"69cff3e81701d3702c9ec4ac","author":"undefined","coverImage":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dexy2tumo/image/upload/v1775236072/books/covers/x5tenqgpdbcrzoeutk6g.jpg","createdAt":"2026-04-03T17:07:52.237Z","description":"Vincent Mboya Mulwa that explores what the author sees as a serious moral and doctrinal crisis facing the Christian church today, especially in the Kenyan context.\r\n\r\nIn the book, Mulwa argues that traditional Christian teaching on marriage and sexual morality has been challenged by changing social realities — such as the high number of unmarried adults and shifting attitudes toward sexuality — and that the church is at a “crossroads” in deciding how to respond. He examines questions around marriage, sexual ethics, and cultural norms, and discusses how Christianity should navigate these challenges without losing its core beliefs.\r\n\r\nThe title — “at the crossroads” — reflects the idea that the Christian faith is at a critical decision point between competing paths, and Mulwa attempts to offer theological and practical insight into how believers can find a way forward that is faithful to Scripture and relevant to contemporary issues","fileUrl":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dexy2tumo/raw/upload/v1775236070/books/files/te3rwez5znjkmfgccxnn","price":200,"title":"Christianity at the crossroads","updatedAt":"2026-04-07T12:16:13.264Z"},{"__v":0,"_id":"69cff35a1701d3702c9ec4a9","author":"Rev Vincent Mboya","coverImage":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dexy2tumo/image/upload/v1775235930/books/covers/j9lskmc6v6m9hlqj1xfp.jpg","createdAt":"2026-04-03T17:05:30.189Z","description":"Doctrinary would be a book that delves into the core teachings or doctrines of a belief system, explaining why those doctrines matter, how they developed, and how they should be applied. It would emphasize firm adherence to foundational principles, and argue for understanding and following those doctrines carefully rather than flexibly.","fileUrl":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dexy2tumo/raw/upload/v1775235928/books/files/mhirdyd7lhe6jdvrnfcg","price":200,"title":"The doctrinally","updatedAt":"2026-04-07T12:16:24.014Z"},{"__v":0,"_id":"69cff0bf1701d3702c9ec47d","author":"Rev Vincent Mboya","coverImage":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dexy2tumo/image/upload/v1775235263/books/covers/xkalsxnrzuuchqelkaxn.jpg","createdAt":"2026-04-03T16:54:23.497Z","description":"The author argues that in many communities, attention and resources have focused heavily on empowering girls and women — which has been important — but boys and men have not received the same level of emotional or societal support.\r\nMulwa suggests this neglect has contributed to a sense of irrelevance or frustration among boys and young men, affecting their confidence, behavior, and roles in church, family, and society.\r\nThe book discusses how biblical teachings can help boys and men understand their identity, purpose, and responsibilities as envisioned in Christian faith.\r\nIt also encourages a balance where both boys and girls are supported — not in competition, but in a way that values each gender’s potential and contribution.","fileUrl":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dexy2tumo/raw/upload/v1775235262/books/files/wzvqzwa4lx4neguoct0c","price":200,"title":"Empowering boy child","updatedAt":"2026-04-07T12:16:33.938Z"}]
